hopobject.body: Would you like to leave a message? bestchinesemedicines.com On Tuesday the U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service (FWS) made its final review of a proposed experiment in three states to determine whether killing barred owls will aid populations of northern spotted owls, which have faced the threat of extinction after decades of habitat loss, and more recently threats from barred owls. Barred owls are larger and more aggressive than northern spotted owls, which has led to the smaller birds being bested in competition for food and territory.
